                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b/82: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Portuguese Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alte</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="79b" xml:id="d269fn79b">At Bar Harbor, Maine.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed British Minister at Lisbon is opposing applications of
                    Western Union Telegraph Company and Commercial <pb facs="0474" n="360"
                        xml:id="pg_360"/> Cable Company for concessions to land and operate cables
                    at Azores.</p>
                <p>This Government is deeply interested in having favorable and prompt action taken
                    on applications of American companies and would appreciate any action you can
                    take to that end.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
